WEBVTT

1
00:00:48.872 --> 00:00:53.872
Subtitles by explosiveskull
www.OpenSubtitles.org

3
00:01:03.925 --> 00:01:05.969
I'm heading there with my sister's family.

4
00:01:06.511 --> 00:01:08.179
We're almost there. so hang on.

5
00:01:12.517 --> 00:01:14.102
Is this the right way?

6
00:01:14.394 --> 00:01:16.229
I drove through here dozens of times.

7
00:01:16.896 --> 00:01:18.732
All the other roads would be packed with cars.

8
00:01:26.114 --> 00:01:27.240
Oh...

9
00:01:30.452 --> 00:01:32.829
Please give us a ride.

10
00:01:33.580 --> 00:01:36.666
I have a little girl. I have a wife too.

11
00:01:37.291 --> 00:01:39.252
Please take us to the port.

12
00:01:40.795 --> 00:01:42.130
I'm begging you...

13
00:01:42.213 --> 00:01:44.633
I wasn't bitten! It's not a bite!

14
00:01:49.763 --> 00:01:53.307
If we look dangerous.
at least take our girl. Please.

15
00:01:53.392 --> 00:01:54.934
Sir?

16
00:01:55.644 --> 00:01:57.854
Please! I'm begging you!

17
00:01:58.605 --> 00:01:59.773
Sir! Please!

18
00:02:03.192 --> 00:02:04.361
Jung-seok...

19
00:02:05.904 --> 00:02:07.489
Don't say anything until we're on the ship!

20
00:02:14.996 --> 00:02:18.291
Can you tell us
why this dreadful virus has spread. Paul?

21
00:02:18.708 --> 00:02:21.127
Well. unfortunately. we don't have much information

22
00:02:21.335 --> 00:02:24.756
other than the fact that it started
out of a bio-factory in South Korea.

23
00:02:24.839 --> 00:02:29.553
Uh. it's unclear exactly
how this unidentified virus initially began to spread.

24
00:02:30.136 --> 00:02:33.390
Of course.
sheer pandemonium broke loose in South Korea.

25
00:02:33.723 --> 00:02:35.975
And many people began to believe a rumor

26
00:02:36.059 --> 00:02:37.394
that was circulating online

27
00:02:37.477 --> 00:02:39.729
{\an8}about a safe region somewhere further down south...

28
00:02:39.813 --> 00:02:42.231
{\an8}Busan? Is this the correct pronunciation?

29
00:02:42.315 --> 00:02:44.568
{\an8}That's right. People were evacuated there.

30
00:02:44.651 --> 00:02:47.404
{\an8}But in the end. no place was truly safe.

31
00:02:47.487 --> 00:02:51.199
{\an8}But there is an absolute safe place
on the Korean Peninsula.

32
00:02:51.282 --> 00:02:54.243
That's correct.
I believe you're referring to North Korea.

33
00:02:54.828 --> 00:02:58.081
Perhaps it's fortunate
that this happened before the reunification!

34
00:02:58.164 --> 00:02:59.416
So it turns out.

35
00:02:59.749 --> 00:03:03.378
So how long before the Korean government
lost all control?

36
00:03:03.462 --> 00:03:05.004
Just one day.

37
00:03:07.298 --> 00:03:09.676
Please move slowly!

38
00:03:10.176 --> 00:03:12.011
This is Alpha One.

39
00:03:13.179 --> 00:03:14.180
Move on!

40
00:03:14.263 --> 00:03:15.264
Be careful!

41
00:03:29.237 --> 00:03:30.279
This is Alpha Two.

42
00:03:30.364 --> 00:03:32.198
We have about 50 civilians waiting for boarding.

43
00:03:48.382 --> 00:03:49.466
Uncle.

44
00:03:53.177 --> 00:03:54.388
Are you all right. Dong-hwan?

45
00:03:54.804 --> 00:03:55.805
Yes.

46
00:03:56.473 --> 00:03:57.474
Where's Chul-min?

47
00:03:57.891 --> 00:03:59.809
He went to get some relief aid.

48
00:04:00.768 --> 00:04:04.898
But shouldn't we have arrived in Japan by now?

49
00:04:05.857 --> 00:04:08.026
I'm sure we're almost there. don't worry.

50
00:04:09.569 --> 00:04:10.570
Captain!

51
00:04:14.323 --> 00:04:15.324
What is it?

52
00:04:15.409 --> 00:04:17.369
We're being rerouted to Hong Kong.

53
00:04:18.703 --> 00:04:19.704
Why all of sudden?

54
00:04:20.038 --> 00:04:21.540
They're not telling me why.

55
00:04:23.917 --> 00:04:25.293
I have to go check something.

56
00:04:38.432 --> 00:04:39.558
Excuse me.

57
00:04:41.726 --> 00:04:43.812
I'll ask about it.
so go and check what's going on.

58
00:04:43.895 --> 00:04:44.896
Yes. sir.

59
00:04:45.522 --> 00:04:46.565
Excuse me.

60
00:04:46.981 --> 00:04:47.982
Excuse me.

61
00:04:54.698 --> 00:04:55.699
Uh.

62
00:05:24.769 --> 00:05:25.812
Sir!

63
00:05:27.188 --> 00:05:28.189
Sir!

64
00:05:28.482 --> 00:05:30.609
Is it true that we are rerouting to Hong Kong?

65
00:05:30.692 --> 00:05:32.486
Please return to your seats.

66
00:05:32.986 --> 00:05:35.071
We need to understand the situation. sir!

67
00:05:35.947 --> 00:05:37.449
Everyone's getting nervous.

68
00:05:37.741 --> 00:05:41.119
Please return to your seat
and await further instructions.

69
00:05:41.202 --> 00:05:42.245
Sir!

70
00:05:42.371 --> 00:05:43.372
We have a problem.

71
00:05:43.455 --> 00:05:45.749
We've found an infected person
on the lower deck cabins.

72
00:05:47.333 --> 00:05:48.334
We get ramen too?

73
00:05:50.879 --> 00:05:52.589
Come in. Leave your bag here.

74
00:05:52.672 --> 00:05:53.673
It looks good.

75
00:05:53.840 --> 00:05:54.841
Please come in.

76
00:05:55.299 --> 00:05:56.635
- Infected!
- What?

77
00:06:01.305 --> 00:06:02.349
What is it?

78
00:06:57.821 --> 00:06:59.573
It's okay. I'll be right here.

79
00:07:00.073 --> 00:07:03.493
Breathe. Dong-hwan. I'm not going anywhere.

80
00:07:03.993 --> 00:07:05.161
It'll be okay.

81
00:07:05.412 --> 00:07:07.246
Look at me.

82
00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:14.128
I'll be right here with you.

83
00:07:18.216 --> 00:07:20.677
What do I do?

84
00:07:22.429 --> 00:07:24.848
Your uncle's here. Dong-hwan.

85
00:07:29.227 --> 00:07:30.228
Sis...

86
00:07:30.645 --> 00:07:32.606
- What do we do?
- We have to go.

87
00:07:32.689 --> 00:07:34.023
We have to go now. come on!

88
00:07:35.567 --> 00:07:37.361
- Let's go!
- Your uncle...

89
00:07:39.153 --> 00:07:40.196
We have to go!

90
00:07:41.490 --> 00:07:42.616
We must leave.

91
00:07:42.699 --> 00:07:43.700
Come on!

92
00:07:45.535 --> 00:07:46.578
Sis!

93
00:08:04.095 --> 00:08:06.305
Sis! Sis!

94
00:08:20.819 --> 00:08:21.863
Honey!

95
00:08:23.196 --> 00:08:24.197
No!

96
00:08:58.983 --> 00:09:01.486
There is even a case of infected hosts

97
00:09:01.570 --> 00:09:04.448
that were found on the last lifeboats
to leave for Hong Kong.

98
00:09:04.531 --> 00:09:06.199
After that. the neighboring countries

99
00:09:06.282 --> 00:09:09.453
decided to no longer accept any more refugees.

100
00:09:09.536 --> 00:09:12.246
In effect. Korea became completely quarantined.

101
00:09:12.664 --> 00:09:14.541
Yes. it's been four years already.

102
00:09:14.624 --> 00:09:16.334
Yes. Four years.

103
00:10:23.276 --> 00:10:24.486
Wake him up.

104
00:10:29.032 --> 00:10:31.493
Hey! Wake up!

105
00:10:35.955 --> 00:10:36.998
That's enough!

106
00:10:40.377 --> 00:10:41.920
We are not here to fight.

107
00:10:42.336 --> 00:10:43.755
The boss wants to see you.

108
00:10:46.925 --> 00:10:47.967
Hey!

109
00:11:22.877 --> 00:11:23.878
Come on.

110
00:11:32.095 --> 00:11:33.347
What are you doing here?

111
00:11:33.597 --> 00:11:34.598
Let's leave.

112
00:11:34.681 --> 00:11:35.682
Let go of me.

113
00:11:36.350 --> 00:11:37.351
Hyung!

114
00:11:37.476 --> 00:11:38.477
"Hyung."

115
00:11:40.520 --> 00:11:42.063
It means "brother." doesn't it?

116
00:11:42.271 --> 00:11:43.648
You two brothers? Huh?

117
00:11:43.898 --> 00:11:45.066
No. no. no.

118
00:11:45.149 --> 00:11:47.361
He is my dead wife's brother.

119
00:11:47.736 --> 00:11:48.945
Not brother.

120
00:11:49.946 --> 00:11:51.948
That sounds like a real tragic story.

121
00:11:53.992 --> 00:11:55.034
Have a seat.

122
00:11:55.619 --> 00:11:57.245
I don't know what the hell is it
with you people from the peninsula?

123
00:11:57.328 --> 00:12:00.874
You. uh... have an air about you.

124
00:12:01.458 --> 00:12:03.710
You have a lot of sad. sad tales...

125
00:12:04.168 --> 00:12:06.129
Let's get down to business.

126
00:12:06.588 --> 00:12:09.466
Should I say "your country"
or "the peninsula"?

127
00:12:10.049 --> 00:12:12.093
Look. I. I heard a rumor...

128
00:12:12.552 --> 00:12:15.972
There seems to be some people
that are going back down

129
00:12:16.055 --> 00:12:19.351
into the peninsula
to make their own fate.

130
00:12:20.184 --> 00:12:23.438
Zombies don't give a damn about all
that gold and money.

131
00:12:23.522 --> 00:12:26.315
which is just laying around there unguarded.

132
00:12:27.275 --> 00:12:28.818
I think it's ingenious.

133
00:12:28.902 --> 00:12:29.944
Wow.

134
00:12:31.320 --> 00:12:32.739
You want us to go back in there?

135
00:12:33.823 --> 00:12:35.324
Have you lost your mind?

136
00:12:36.034 --> 00:12:37.243
My brother.

137
00:12:37.994 --> 00:12:41.039
my mind is completely sound. thank you.

138
00:12:41.330 --> 00:12:42.331
Okay.

139
00:12:42.916 --> 00:12:43.958
So...

140
00:12:44.918 --> 00:12:47.336
the neighboring countries around the peninsula

141
00:12:47.421 --> 00:12:50.590
are controlling every ship
and plane that crosses the border.

142
00:12:51.633 --> 00:12:53.635
How would you get in or out?

143
00:12:54.761 --> 00:12:56.012
It's been done.

144
00:12:56.471 --> 00:12:58.807
You don't need to worry about the coast guard.

145
00:12:59.558 --> 00:13:01.267
As long as we keep paying them.

146
00:13:01.351 --> 00:13:03.645
the ships go in. the ships go out.

147
00:13:04.228 --> 00:13:07.774
As a matter of fact. technically.
we had the money and the truck.

148
00:13:08.400 --> 00:13:10.151
Twenty million dollars.

149
00:13:10.234 --> 00:13:11.820
Until we went missing halfway here.

150
00:13:11.903 --> 00:13:13.154
Where was the last time we...

151
00:13:13.237 --> 00:13:14.489
On the Omok Bridge.

152
00:13:14.614 --> 00:13:15.615
Mok-dong?

153
00:13:16.700 --> 00:13:17.701
What?

154
00:13:17.784 --> 00:13:19.243
Look. I don't think it's too difficult.

155
00:13:19.327 --> 00:13:20.912
You just go in at night.

156
00:13:20.995 --> 00:13:23.415
you get the truck. come back with the money.

157
00:13:23.498 --> 00:13:26.125
and don't worry about those zombies.

158
00:13:26.209 --> 00:13:28.878
I hear they are practically blind at night.

159
00:13:29.421 --> 00:13:30.505
So...

160
00:13:31.548 --> 00:13:33.467
How much money we get?

161
00:13:33.717 --> 00:13:34.718
Yeah. yeah. yeah.

162
00:13:36.386 --> 00:13:38.347
Well. that's the question. isn't it?

163
00:13:38.763 --> 00:13:39.764
Half.

164
00:13:40.932 --> 00:13:43.727
That is. if you come back alive.

165
00:13:44.603 --> 00:13:48.523
That's 2.5 million dollars per head.

166
00:13:49.524 --> 00:13:50.734
Now listen to me.

167
00:13:50.900 --> 00:13:53.695
You have no idea when or even

168
00:13:53.903 --> 00:13:58.992
if the government is ever going
to grant you any refugee status.

169
00:13:59.075 --> 00:14:02.371
so you might as well make your own goddamn future.

170
00:14:02.454 --> 00:14:03.455
Think!

171
00:14:14.924 --> 00:14:19.053
We just have to hop on a boat.
and bring the truck back.

172
00:14:19.137 --> 00:14:20.472
What's so hard about that?

173
00:14:20.930 --> 00:14:22.557
It'll only take half a day.

174
00:14:27.396 --> 00:14:30.023
Are you nuts? You want to go back there?

175
00:14:33.485 --> 00:14:35.904
Then do you want to keep living here.
getting treated like scum?

176
00:14:40.450 --> 00:14:43.537
You should have let me die
with my son and wife!

177
00:14:44.037 --> 00:14:45.204
Why did you do it?

178
00:14:46.205 --> 00:14:49.793
Had I let you die. everyone on
that ship would've died.

179
00:14:49.876 --> 00:14:50.877
Am I wrong?

180
00:14:53.129 --> 00:14:54.548
It was a sensible decision.

181
00:14:56.425 --> 00:14:58.217
Sensible decision. my ass.

182
00:14:59.969 --> 00:15:01.220
Did you even try?

183
00:15:03.848 --> 00:15:04.891
Jung-seok...

184
00:15:06.309 --> 00:15:07.977
You're tormented too!

185
00:15:09.896 --> 00:15:11.606
You just gave up!

186
00:15:16.069 --> 00:15:18.655
Whatever. forget it.

187
00:15:18.988 --> 00:15:19.989
Okay.

188
00:15:20.949 --> 00:15:23.868
Well. I'm going to go there.

189
00:15:23.952 --> 00:15:27.456
so you can do whatever you want.

190
00:15:28.206 --> 00:15:30.625
Let's just not bump into each other.

191
00:15:31.460 --> 00:15:32.919
It's hard for both of us.

192
00:15:33.628 --> 00:15:35.213
Bye-bye. Bye-bye.

193
00:15:35.964 --> 00:15:38.550
Aren't they bastards from the peninsula?

194
00:15:38.633 --> 00:15:40.844
- What?
- Where the virus came from!

195
00:15:41.345 --> 00:15:43.472
Should you be letting them in here?

196
00:15:43.555 --> 00:15:44.556
Move aside.

197
00:15:44.639 --> 00:15:45.724
- Let go of me.
- Stop.

198
00:15:45.807 --> 00:15:47.266
Do you even care about the others?

199
00:15:47.351 --> 00:15:48.393
Stop it.

200
00:15:48.477 --> 00:15:51.020
Is he infected?

201
00:15:51.104 --> 00:15:52.606
Come on. Stop.

202
00:15:52.731 --> 00:15:54.649
I won't take your money. so just leave!

203
00:15:56.234 --> 00:15:57.402
You go ahead.

204
00:16:30.560 --> 00:16:32.687
You're entering the peninsula waters.

205
00:16:32.771 --> 00:16:33.897
Turn back.

206
00:16:34.230 --> 00:16:36.024
You're entering the peninsula waters.

207
00:16:36.107 --> 00:16:37.108
Turn back.

208
00:16:37.191 --> 00:16:39.944
This is Z055 Chungpyung.

209
00:16:42.531 --> 00:16:44.658
- Hello?
- Hello?

210
00:16:45.575 --> 00:16:47.243
It's all good if there's no response.

211
00:17:09.432 --> 00:17:10.892
Almost there!

212
00:17:13.812 --> 00:17:16.105
No need to be so serious.

213
00:17:16.189 --> 00:17:18.191
Soon. you'll be rich!

214
00:17:18.900 --> 00:17:20.151
Take what you need.

215
00:17:21.027 --> 00:17:25.365
Don't forget. the zombies are blind at night
and sensitive to sound.

216
00:17:26.240 --> 00:17:27.617
And the important thing.

217
00:17:28.159 --> 00:17:33.206
We'll drop you off
and stay at sea nearby for three days.

218
00:17:37.752 --> 00:17:38.837
Take these.

219
00:17:39.796 --> 00:17:40.797
One for you.

220
00:17:41.381 --> 00:17:44.468
And... another.

221
00:17:45.677 --> 00:17:47.804
Call me when you get to the port with the truck

222
00:17:47.887 --> 00:17:49.848
and we'll pull up the boat.

223
00:17:54.478 --> 00:17:55.729
And lastly!

224
00:17:56.355 --> 00:17:59.858
You escaped out of there alive.
so you know better...

225
00:18:00.400 --> 00:18:03.653
Don't screw up trying
to save each other for nothing.

226
00:18:04.112 --> 00:18:06.072
Don't worry. We know.

227
00:18:06.490 --> 00:18:07.491
Great!

228
00:18:08.157 --> 00:18:09.325
Do not let us down.

229
00:18:18.710 --> 00:18:22.171
It makes me nervous that you two know each other.

230
00:18:22.255 --> 00:18:23.632
I know.

231
00:18:24.383 --> 00:18:26.426
We have to pull this off no matter what.

232
00:18:26.510 --> 00:18:28.845
so don't let your personal emotions
get mixed up in the way.

233
00:18:29.220 --> 00:18:32.181
We won't even see each other after this.
so don't worry.

234
00:18:33.892 --> 00:18:34.934
Fine.

235
00:18:35.477 --> 00:18:36.561
Whatever. man.

236
00:20:01.730 --> 00:20:08.695
GOD HAS FORSAKEN US

237
00:20:29.257 --> 00:20:30.592
We're not on a tour. you know.

238
00:20:31.593 --> 00:20:34.721
Let's hurry things along.
we should leave before sunrise.

239
00:20:35.472 --> 00:20:37.140
All right. let's get it over with.

240
00:20:37.223 --> 00:20:38.725
Jeez.

241
00:20:43.522 --> 00:20:44.689
Is it working?

242
00:20:47.233 --> 00:20:48.610
Nice!

243
00:21:09.756 --> 00:21:11.841
It's unrecognizable now. My goodness.

244
00:21:12.341 --> 00:21:15.219
The city became a ruin in just four years.

245
00:21:15.970 --> 00:21:17.263
Did you live near here?

246
00:21:18.264 --> 00:21:21.142
I used to drive a cab.

247
00:21:21.643 --> 00:21:24.312
So I pretty much know all the roads.

248
00:21:25.564 --> 00:21:28.191
At the very least.
those jerks put together a good team.

249
00:21:39.243 --> 00:21:41.204
A HEALTHY. CAREFREE COUNTRY

250
00:22:04.143 --> 00:22:05.395
Could that be it?

251
00:22:05.645 --> 00:22:06.813
Where?

252
00:22:08.272 --> 00:22:10.108
The plate number is 6431. right?

253
00:22:10.692 --> 00:22:11.901
We'll find out soon.

254
00:22:12.486 --> 00:22:14.404
You stay here. I'll go alone.

255
00:22:14.488 --> 00:22:15.530
What?

256
00:22:15.614 --> 00:22:17.491
Hey. hey. hey! Wait!

257
00:23:23.848 --> 00:23:25.099
Come on. come on. come on!

258
00:23:26.267 --> 00:23:27.519
What's with you?

259
00:23:28.353 --> 00:23:29.521
Is that the truck?

260
00:23:30.271 --> 00:23:31.398
No. it isn't.

261
00:23:33.107 --> 00:23:35.234
It should be nearby.
Let's look around a bit more.

262
00:24:03.137 --> 00:24:05.557
There. I see one more.

263
00:24:07.434 --> 00:24:08.768
Let's check it out.

264
00:24:09.936 --> 00:24:11.187
Okay.

265
00:24:30.123 --> 00:24:33.835
I'll go have a look. You stay here.

266
00:24:33.918 --> 00:24:34.919
Stop it!

267
00:24:35.379 --> 00:24:36.671
I'm not on a tour. you know.

268
00:24:37.464 --> 00:24:38.590
We'll go together.

269
00:24:39.132 --> 00:24:40.133
Mister.

270
00:24:40.550 --> 00:24:42.301
Let's take a look.

271
00:25:03.823 --> 00:25:05.199
Are they Unit 631?

272
00:25:06.618 --> 00:25:09.245
No. They're not.

273
00:25:11.498 --> 00:25:13.417
Jackpot. we found it.

274
00:25:39.108 --> 00:25:40.193
It was true...

275
00:25:43.572 --> 00:25:45.574
What they said was true.

276
00:25:45.657 --> 00:25:47.784
It's all in US dollars. How much is all this?

277
00:25:48.618 --> 00:25:50.370
We confirmed it. so let's get going.

278
00:25:52.456 --> 00:25:53.457
Okay.

279
00:25:54.791 --> 00:25:55.792
Jeez.

280
00:25:57.627 --> 00:25:59.921
Hey! Over here!

281
00:26:02.716 --> 00:26:05.719
He must've been the last person to make contact.

282
00:26:08.262 --> 00:26:09.973
How unfortunate.

283
00:26:10.474 --> 00:26:12.434
He could've been a millionaire.

284
00:26:12.809 --> 00:26:14.394
But it's good for us.

285
00:26:14.686 --> 00:26:16.145
Let's pull him out and go.

286
00:26:18.607 --> 00:26:20.817
Oh. jeez...

287
00:26:22.026 --> 00:26:23.027
He stinks...

288
00:26:24.946 --> 00:26:27.198
Move your leg. Thank you.

289
00:26:27.699 --> 00:26:28.742
Thank you.

290
00:26:39.378 --> 00:26:40.379
Idiots.

291
00:26:50.179 --> 00:26:51.222
Are you okay?

292
00:26:51.681 --> 00:26:53.392
I'm fine. I wasn't bitten.

293
00:27:01.650 --> 00:27:04.027
Gosh. what are they up to?

294
00:27:18.750 --> 00:27:20.043
Get in the car. go!

295
00:27:22.921 --> 00:27:24.005
Back it up!

296
00:28:15.098 --> 00:28:16.350
Hurry. hurry. hurry!

297
00:28:16.433 --> 00:28:17.476
Come on. come on. come on!

298
00:28:17.559 --> 00:28:18.643
All right!

299
00:28:20.604 --> 00:28:21.355
Let's go!

300
00:28:21.355 --> 00:28:22.647
Go! Go!

301
00:28:30.864 --> 00:28:32.031
We're clear. we're clear!

302
00:28:32.240 --> 00:28:33.367
Thank you...

303
00:28:34.283 --> 00:28:36.870
So the money's really there?

304
00:28:37.912 --> 00:28:39.914
You're a millionaire!

305
00:28:42.125 --> 00:28:43.167
Yes!

306
00:28:43.251 --> 00:28:44.878
Awesome!

307
00:28:45.253 --> 00:28:46.588
What will you do with the money?

308
00:28:46.671 --> 00:28:48.131
Me? Uh...

309
00:28:48.214 --> 00:28:49.340
Maybe I'll hire a chauffeur.

310
00:28:49.424 --> 00:28:51.175
Like a real millionaire!

311
00:28:55.096 --> 00:28:57.098
So we just have to get
to the harbor and call them in.

312
00:28:58.558 --> 00:29:00.477
This is a piece of cake!

313
00:29:02.437 --> 00:29:03.647
Give me the satellite phone.

314
00:29:03.730 --> 00:29:05.440
Huh? Sure. hold on.

315
00:29:17.494 --> 00:29:19.245
Here.

316
00:29:21.665 --> 00:29:22.916
What's that?

317
00:29:43.978 --> 00:29:45.021
Just drive!

318
00:29:45.229 --> 00:29:47.023
Go. go. go! Just go!

319
00:31:33.337 --> 00:31:34.589
Hop in. if you want to live.

320
00:31:40.887 --> 00:31:41.930
Sorry!

321
00:32:09.541 --> 00:32:10.917
You must've been scared.

322
00:32:11.918 --> 00:32:16.214
Yu-jin. I told you not
to act so friendly to strangers.

323
00:32:17.382 --> 00:32:18.592
Sit back properly.

324
00:34:08.868 --> 00:34:10.286
Dang. he passed out.

325
00:34:11.120 --> 00:34:12.956
Did I not tell him to buckle up?

326
00:34:17.544 --> 00:34:20.296
Joon-i. can you drive through them?

327
00:34:22.424 --> 00:34:23.467
I'm not sure.

328
00:34:24.509 --> 00:34:27.346
Then what? Do I need to get involved?

329
00:35:16.269 --> 00:35:17.479
Ooh...

330
00:35:17.562 --> 00:35:18.938
Ooh.

331
00:35:29.616 --> 00:35:30.825
Uh?

332
00:35:39.167 --> 00:35:40.251
Really?

333
00:35:40.960 --> 00:35:44.381
The ground was weird. it wasn't my fault.

334
00:35:45.715 --> 00:35:47.216
Oh.

335
00:36:19.458 --> 00:36:22.001
I really liked that one. though.

336
00:36:49.153 --> 00:36:51.531
CITY NIGHT CLUB

337
00:37:33.573 --> 00:37:35.992
It's a grocery truck. Nice.

338
00:37:36.910 --> 00:37:38.286
It looks new.

339
00:37:43.207 --> 00:37:45.209
- Who's that?
- He's alive!

340
00:37:47.837 --> 00:37:50.590
- Please. help me...
- Be careful.

341
00:37:50.799 --> 00:37:54.386
- Be careful.
- Help me. I'm begging you...

342
00:37:58.181 --> 00:38:00.016
Help me. please.

343
00:38:00.099 --> 00:38:01.726
What the hell's going on?

344
00:38:02.226 --> 00:38:03.645
He's just an infected. you jerks.

345
00:38:03.770 --> 00:38:05.271
Have you never seen one before?

346
00:38:05.814 --> 00:38:06.815
Please...

347
00:38:06.898 --> 00:38:08.692
It's all right. come here.

348
00:38:29.253 --> 00:38:33.883
Sir. please. help me...

349
00:38:33.967 --> 00:38:36.553
I'm begging you...

350
00:38:40.599 --> 00:38:42.684
- Give it to me.
- Here you go!

351
00:38:45.520 --> 00:38:46.896
Sir...

352
00:38:50.108 --> 00:38:51.485
Nice shot!

353
00:38:51.693 --> 00:38:53.236
Wow. he killed him properly.

354
00:38:54.028 --> 00:38:55.154
Damn it!

355
00:38:57.115 --> 00:38:59.158
It got on my pants. I should get it washed.

356
00:38:59.826 --> 00:39:00.827
Here.

357
00:39:01.995 --> 00:39:03.246
Let's get back. the sun will rise.

358
00:39:03.788 --> 00:39:04.789
Shit...

359
00:39:05.164 --> 00:39:07.626
- Let's go.
- The zombies are coming!

360
00:39:10.169 --> 00:39:11.880
Huh?

361
00:39:32.817 --> 00:39:34.444
You little rascals!

362
00:39:34.778 --> 00:39:38.031
You brought something dangerous instead
of what you were supposed to get.

363
00:39:38.156 --> 00:39:39.198
Hey!

364
00:39:39.783 --> 00:39:43.327
You'd have been locked up for insubordination
if it were the old days!

365
00:39:50.043 --> 00:39:51.335
Lieutenant Yoon! Captain Hwang!

366
00:39:51.420 --> 00:39:52.421
Assemble!

367
00:39:52.921 --> 00:39:54.338
Aren't you going to make a report?

368
00:39:54.423 --> 00:39:55.924
Did you get what I asked?

369
00:39:56.215 --> 00:39:58.885
Salute! Division commander. we did not get it!

370
00:40:00.845 --> 00:40:01.846
Hey!

371
00:40:02.180 --> 00:40:03.515
How could you not get it?

372
00:40:03.598 --> 00:40:05.809
The ROK-US Combined Forces Command
is waiting for my call!

373
00:40:05.892 --> 00:40:07.185
Without batteries...

374
00:40:07.268 --> 00:40:08.395
Come on!

375
00:40:08.478 --> 00:40:10.063
- Are you having fun?
- Joon-i!

376
00:40:10.605 --> 00:40:12.148
- Captain Hwang!
- Grandpa!

377
00:40:12.774 --> 00:40:14.693
How long will you go on with that army stuff?

378
00:40:14.776 --> 00:40:15.777
Aren't you sick of it?

379
00:40:15.860 --> 00:40:17.111
No. it's for real this time!

380
00:40:17.195 --> 00:40:19.781
The newly appointed Major Jane
is totally different.

381
00:40:19.864 --> 00:40:21.491
She and I get along.

382
00:40:21.575 --> 00:40:24.536
And it seems like we'll get rescued soon.

383
00:40:24.619 --> 00:40:26.996
Listen to me. I'm good friends with her. so--

384
00:40:27.080 --> 00:40:29.040
- Stop it! I'm sick of it!
- Yu-jin. you believe me. right?

385
00:40:29.123 --> 00:40:30.124
Who are you?

386
00:40:33.086 --> 00:40:35.464
I guess you've never experienced
a wild dog hunt before.

387
00:40:35.547 --> 00:40:37.048
You should've known that such trucks

388
00:40:37.131 --> 00:40:38.717
would attract their attention.

389
00:40:39.050 --> 00:40:40.134
"Truck"?

390
00:40:40.218 --> 00:40:41.553
Who's that?

391
00:40:41.636 --> 00:40:42.637
Mom!

392
00:40:47.809 --> 00:40:51.980
Sir! Please!

393
00:40:54.023 --> 00:40:56.693
He was almost caught by Unit 631.

394
00:40:57.902 --> 00:40:59.278
You went outside again?

395
00:40:59.904 --> 00:41:01.615
I convinced her to go.

396
00:41:01.698 --> 00:41:03.282
Why don't you ever listen to me?

397
00:41:05.076 --> 00:41:06.244
I'm sorry. Mom.

398
00:41:07.996 --> 00:41:10.582
They're batteries. Grandpa. she got batteries!

399
00:41:12.291 --> 00:41:14.210
Okay! Okay!

400
00:41:16.921 --> 00:41:17.922
They fit.

401
00:41:18.006 --> 00:41:20.008
Hi. Jane? Jane? Major Jane?

402
00:41:20.592 --> 00:41:23.136
Oh. Jane! Oh. Jane! Okay!

403
00:41:24.971 --> 00:41:26.180
Are you okay?

404
00:41:26.264 --> 00:41:28.892
- I'm okay! Yeah!
- You should turn it on.

405
00:41:28.975 --> 00:41:30.394
We are strong soldiers! No problem!

406
00:41:30.477 --> 00:41:31.728
I'm Yu-jin!

407
00:41:34.022 --> 00:41:35.106
When are you coming?

408
00:41:35.189 --> 00:41:37.442
- So people still live here...
- They said they're coming!

409
00:41:39.235 --> 00:41:40.319
Who are you?

410
00:41:40.945 --> 00:41:42.280
Are you with Unit 631?

411
00:41:46.242 --> 00:41:48.286
I don't know what 631 is.

412
00:41:50.121 --> 00:41:52.331
I came to Incheon by boat yesterday.

413
00:41:53.542 --> 00:41:54.709
From Hong Kong.

414
00:41:55.168 --> 00:41:56.169
What?

415
00:41:57.295 --> 00:41:58.755
From where?

416
00:42:09.974 --> 00:42:11.685
Damn. the sun is rising.

417
00:42:13.102 --> 00:42:14.771
Let's hurry up.

418
00:42:19.943 --> 00:42:21.445
The third platoon is returning!

419
00:42:21.528 --> 00:42:22.904
Open the gate!

420
00:42:32.664 --> 00:42:35.124
There are one. two. three.
four. five. six boxes of cookies.

421
00:42:35.500 --> 00:42:36.710
That's all correct.

422
00:42:39.087 --> 00:42:40.422
Scrap soup again?

423
00:42:40.714 --> 00:42:41.840
Eat if you want to live.

424
00:42:41.923 --> 00:42:45.009
That looks good. Have a great meal!

425
00:42:45.093 --> 00:42:47.053
Have a nice meal. Have a nice meal.

426
00:42:49.263 --> 00:42:50.890
The third platoon is back!

427
00:42:50.974 --> 00:42:52.308
They're here!

428
00:43:02.276 --> 00:43:05.989
- They're back!
- They're here!

429
00:43:07.657 --> 00:43:09.868
Great work. everyone.

430
00:43:09.951 --> 00:43:11.620
Look! Isn't it awesome?

431
00:43:11.703 --> 00:43:13.329
- Yeah!
- It sure is.

432
00:43:13.413 --> 00:43:15.039
My boys worked so hard!

433
00:43:15.123 --> 00:43:17.459
Bring us a can of tuna. that's all I ask!

434
00:43:17.542 --> 00:43:18.752
- I'm sorry. sir...
- No. bring one.

435
00:43:18.835 --> 00:43:20.462
We were told to keep a tight lid on supplies.

436
00:43:20.545 --> 00:43:23.006
If I keep handing out stuff.
there won't be anything left.

437
00:43:23.089 --> 00:43:24.298
And Captain Seo is...

438
00:43:24.883 --> 00:43:26.050
One can is too much?

439
00:43:26.300 --> 00:43:27.301
That's not it...

440
00:43:27.636 --> 00:43:28.637
Bring it.

441
00:43:28.887 --> 00:43:29.929
They're serving food at the cafeteria.

442
00:43:30.013 --> 00:43:31.014
Get it!

443
00:43:31.097 --> 00:43:32.181
I said bring it!

444
00:43:32.432 --> 00:43:33.850
So I should just have scraps?

445
00:43:34.100 --> 00:43:35.143
That's not...

446
00:43:35.226 --> 00:43:36.227
Do you want it?

447
00:43:36.561 --> 00:43:38.688
I have to report to Captain Seo first.

448
00:43:39.313 --> 00:43:40.774
Just bring it. asshole!

449
00:43:41.983 --> 00:43:46.029
Report to a guy who's never even fought before?

450
00:43:46.446 --> 00:43:47.781
He's my commander.

451
00:43:47.864 --> 00:43:49.908
- Sergeant...
- Piss off. you bastard!

452
00:43:51.576 --> 00:43:53.327
- What was that?
- I'm talking here!

453
00:43:53.703 --> 00:43:55.204
- What was that?
- Hello?

454
00:43:55.622 --> 00:43:58.542
- Where is it coming from?
- I heard something.

455
00:44:01.545 --> 00:44:03.004
- What? A person?
- Hang on.

456
00:44:03.087 --> 00:44:05.632
Sir. we have a wild dog here.

457
00:44:06.466 --> 00:44:07.467
- What?
- Get him.

458
00:44:07.759 --> 00:44:09.052
What's a wild dog?

459
00:44:11.388 --> 00:44:12.764
Are you soldiers?

460
00:44:13.264 --> 00:44:15.642
Help me. I'm not from here.

461
00:44:16.768 --> 00:44:17.769
Get up. you bastard.

462
00:44:17.852 --> 00:44:19.312
Has the game started?

463
00:44:19.521 --> 00:44:20.564
It hasn't. sir.

464
00:44:20.647 --> 00:44:22.190
Take him to the arena.

465
00:44:22.273 --> 00:44:24.317
- Yes. sir.
- Let's go!

466
00:44:25.694 --> 00:44:27.404
We have a new player!

467
00:44:32.075 --> 00:44:36.496
Keep sucking up to Captain Seo.
and I'll kill you both.

468
00:44:36.580 --> 00:44:37.581
Got that?

469
00:44:39.583 --> 00:44:41.460
You little...

470
00:44:44.504 --> 00:44:45.630
Hey! Hey!

471
00:44:46.631 --> 00:44:48.049
He probably wasted all the flares

472
00:44:48.132 --> 00:44:49.634
without knowing what to get.

473
00:44:50.134 --> 00:44:51.219
That idiot.

474
00:44:51.636 --> 00:44:55.432
He brought so much useless crap last time.

475
00:45:00.437 --> 00:45:01.646
What the hell?

476
00:45:02.063 --> 00:45:03.857
We are strong soldiers!

477
00:45:04.148 --> 00:45:05.442
Strong! Strong!

478
00:45:06.360 --> 00:45:07.611
Strong. Strong.

479
00:45:08.862 --> 00:45:10.989
No one ever came to rescue us in four years.

480
00:45:12.031 --> 00:45:13.700
but some chump change was all it took?

481
00:45:16.620 --> 00:45:17.954
What about your group?

482
00:45:22.834 --> 00:45:23.918
They're all dead.

483
00:45:25.795 --> 00:45:26.880
Everyone.

484
00:45:29.257 --> 00:45:30.467
We got a fresh one!

485
00:45:45.023 --> 00:45:46.400
Hey there. cutie!

486
00:45:51.738 --> 00:45:53.114
Who were those soldiers?

487
00:45:53.197 --> 00:45:54.866
They're called Unit 631.

488
00:45:55.617 --> 00:45:57.869
They used to be a military unit dispatched
to rescue civilians.

489
00:45:58.412 --> 00:46:00.329
You were with them?

490
00:46:00.414 --> 00:46:02.791
We lived there before we escaped.

491
00:46:02.874 --> 00:46:04.376
At first.

492
00:46:06.169 --> 00:46:07.671
They sent out SOS signals for a few years.

493
00:46:07.754 --> 00:46:08.880
which were left unanswered.

494
00:46:10.089 --> 00:46:12.050
After that. they gave up everything.

495
00:46:12.175 --> 00:46:14.260
and now they're all crazy.

496
00:46:50.296 --> 00:46:51.631
Hm.

497
00:46:52.507 --> 00:46:53.592
I'm leaving.

498
00:47:02.767 --> 00:47:03.768
Yes?

499
00:47:12.569 --> 00:47:15.279
Bang!

500
00:47:16.740 --> 00:47:19.909
Awesome. that's great.

501
00:47:24.038 --> 00:47:26.416
I'm not someone who takes bribes. take it back.

502
00:47:26.541 --> 00:47:28.460
Gosh. you're making me sad.

503
00:47:28.543 --> 00:47:30.587
I don't take bribes!

504
00:47:30.670 --> 00:47:32.005
Look at it. it's Black Label.

505
00:47:33.131 --> 00:47:35.800
Thanks. I was finishing my last drink.

506
00:47:36.718 --> 00:47:39.220
Here. accept my drink.

507
00:47:47.562 --> 00:47:48.897
Nothing to report again?

508
00:47:48.980 --> 00:47:50.524
No. nothing happened.

509
00:47:51.107 --> 00:47:55.612
Sergeant Hwang stole a truck
from wild dogs overnight.

510
00:47:56.154 --> 00:47:59.449
and was boasting like crazy.

511
00:47:59.533 --> 00:48:01.535
acting all high and mighty...

512
00:48:02.369 --> 00:48:05.580
So where did our valiant sergeant go today

513
00:48:05.664 --> 00:48:08.207
and what adventure did he have?

514
00:48:10.334 --> 00:48:11.878
What did he bring in?

515
00:48:12.754 --> 00:48:15.507
Captain. that's the weird thing.

516
00:48:15.965 --> 00:48:17.634
The truck was full of US dollars.

517
00:48:17.717 --> 00:48:18.843
US dollars?

518
00:48:19.886 --> 00:48:20.887
How much?

519
00:48:21.805 --> 00:48:24.015
It was quite a bit.

520
00:48:24.391 --> 00:48:27.477
About 20 bags full of them.

521
00:48:28.061 --> 00:48:31.105
But why do you think those idiotic wild dogs

522
00:48:31.189 --> 00:48:34.359
were transporting completely useless money?

523
00:48:37.111 --> 00:48:38.363
Where is it now?

524
00:48:39.614 --> 00:48:41.408
So they took the truck.

525
00:48:42.158 --> 00:48:43.410
What about the satellite phone?

526
00:48:44.202 --> 00:48:46.245
It should be by the driver's seat.

527
00:48:54.713 --> 00:48:57.757
Sir. I'm not from here!

528
00:48:58.967 --> 00:49:01.052
I'm from Hong Kong!

529
00:49:02.971 --> 00:49:04.055
This is brand new.

530
00:49:04.138 --> 00:49:05.932
It's rare. Today is your lucky day.

531
00:49:06.015 --> 00:49:07.225
Got anything else?

532
00:49:07.476 --> 00:49:10.186
I have... a satellite phone!

533
00:49:11.563 --> 00:49:14.858
With a satellite phone.
we can all get out of here!

534
00:49:15.775 --> 00:49:17.318
- Show us!
- Right here!

535
00:49:17.694 --> 00:49:20.029
- You lying sack of shit!
- He doesn't have it!

536
00:49:25.118 --> 00:49:27.621
Where do you think they
were heading with this money?

537
00:49:34.919 --> 00:49:36.630
Sir. where's the truck?

538
00:49:37.881 --> 00:49:39.215
Stop that!

539
00:49:39.549 --> 00:49:40.800
Stop! Please!

540
00:49:42.844 --> 00:49:44.388
Ah...

541
00:49:52.479 --> 00:49:53.563
He's really fresh!

542
00:49:53.647 --> 00:49:56.733
This guy's in good shape. He's a Grade A!

543
00:50:00.278 --> 00:50:01.405
Can you run well?

544
00:50:01.988 --> 00:50:02.989
No?

545
00:50:06.200 --> 00:50:07.369
What should his number be?

546
00:50:07.452 --> 00:50:08.745
Give him Park Chan-ho's number.

547
00:50:08.828 --> 00:50:09.829
Number 61!

548
00:50:09.913 --> 00:50:11.247
Number 61 it is!

549
00:50:11.330 --> 00:50:15.293
Major League pitcher!

550
00:50:15.960 --> 00:50:17.086
That's a great number!

551
00:50:21.966 --> 00:50:23.092
Turn around!

552
00:50:26.054 --> 00:50:28.432
I'm betting a chocolate bar on him.

553
00:50:33.603 --> 00:50:35.689
Sir. where's the truck?

554
00:50:47.659 --> 00:50:50.954
Sir! I'm not from here!

555
00:50:51.580 --> 00:50:53.540
There's money in the truck! Go check it out!

556
00:50:53.623 --> 00:50:56.501
We can all leave if we have that. you idiots!

557
00:51:17.522 --> 00:51:18.523
What...

558
00:51:23.695 --> 00:51:24.738
Hello?

559
00:51:24.821 --> 00:51:26.322
Where are you? The sun is out.

560
00:51:26.740 --> 00:51:27.866
What's going on?

561
00:51:29.200 --> 00:51:31.370
Hello. Who are you?

562
00:51:31.661 --> 00:51:32.662
What?

563
00:51:32.746 --> 00:51:34.038
Who the hell are you?

564
00:51:34.205 --> 00:51:35.457
Where's the money?

565
00:52:01.816 --> 00:52:03.026
Where are you going?

566
00:52:04.110 --> 00:52:05.445
I don't think we should go out...

567
00:52:09.115 --> 00:52:11.200
Number 61! Get out!

568
00:52:12.952 --> 00:52:14.120
Get the hell out!

569
00:52:47.571 --> 00:52:49.072
I don't care who you are.

570
00:52:49.155 --> 00:52:50.156
Just bring the money.

571
00:52:50.239 --> 00:52:52.534
The terms are the same
as the guys we sent in...

572
00:52:52.784 --> 00:52:55.954
Half the money to anyone
that brings it out. Okay?

573
00:52:56.663 --> 00:53:00.041
Are you saying we can get out of here?

574
00:53:00.124 --> 00:53:02.001
We are waiting around Incheon Port.

575
00:53:02.085 --> 00:53:03.628
You call me when you get there.

576
00:53:04.295 --> 00:53:05.338
It's so easy!

577
00:53:06.130 --> 00:53:08.383
Easy. easy. I can do it. I can do it.

578
00:53:08.467 --> 00:53:09.509
All right.

579
00:53:17.016 --> 00:53:18.518
You can drive. right?

580
00:53:19.686 --> 00:53:21.688
Let's just go now. Mom.

581
00:53:22.647 --> 00:53:24.649
I'll bulldoze them all with my car.

582
00:53:27.276 --> 00:53:30.154
You'll just go in there? In broad daylight?

583
00:54:45.063 --> 00:54:47.315
Run faster!

584
00:55:06.876 --> 00:55:10.880
It's time for us. To say goodbye

585
00:55:11.255 --> 00:55:13.717
Let's meet again soon

586
00:55:15.218 --> 00:55:19.222
It's time for us. To say goodbye

587
00:55:19.556 --> 00:55:22.141
Let's meet again soon

588
00:55:24.853 --> 00:55:26.062
Hey. buddy!

589
00:55:27.271 --> 00:55:28.898
If you don't hurry. the doors will shut!

590
00:55:56.175 --> 00:55:57.427
You must be tired.

591
00:55:57.594 --> 00:55:58.845
You did great.

592
00:55:58.928 --> 00:56:00.304
How about a feast?

593
00:56:00.514 --> 00:56:01.931
You want it? Really?

594
00:56:03.057 --> 00:56:04.726
Have some ramen!

595
00:56:05.143 --> 00:56:07.396
Eat slowly! Share them with your friends!

596
00:56:07.479 --> 00:56:08.772
Greedy bastards.

597
00:56:13.985 --> 00:56:15.111
You should share them!

598
00:56:17.071 --> 00:56:20.367
It's too dangerous now.
Let's move after sundown.

599
00:56:20.450 --> 00:56:23.119
I think we can go now. though...

600
00:56:23.995 --> 00:56:25.580
Go? Go where?

601
00:56:26.956 --> 00:56:29.376
Grandpa. we're moving. Let's pack up.

602
00:56:29.668 --> 00:56:30.710
Move?

603
00:56:31.252 --> 00:56:32.253
Where?

604
00:56:32.336 --> 00:56:34.047
We're going to Incheon Port.

605
00:56:34.130 --> 00:56:35.757
Incheon Port? Are we going to ride a boat?

606
00:56:35.840 --> 00:56:36.841
Okay!

607
00:56:36.925 --> 00:56:38.051
No. no. no!

608
00:56:38.468 --> 00:56:41.846
We must stay here until Jane
comes to rescue us.

609
00:56:41.930 --> 00:56:43.723
It was so hard convincing her!

610
00:56:43.807 --> 00:56:46.476
If Major Jane is coming.
tell her to come to the port.

611
00:56:46.560 --> 00:56:47.894
No way!

612
00:56:47.977 --> 00:56:49.354
You said you two are close.

613
00:56:50.146 --> 00:56:51.690
I guess you aren't.

614
00:56:52.482 --> 00:56:53.483
We're close.

615
00:56:53.692 --> 00:56:55.485
Okay. it's doable.

616
00:56:56.235 --> 00:56:57.696
Incheon? Incheon Port?

617
00:56:57.779 --> 00:56:59.864
- Grandpa. hurry!
- Okay.

618
00:57:02.451 --> 00:57:05.244
You'll take a crazy old man and little kids

619
00:57:06.830 --> 00:57:09.290
to steal a truck from armed soldiers?

620
00:57:10.291 --> 00:57:13.378
Then should I continue living here with my girls?

621
00:57:14.754 --> 00:57:16.631
If you're scared. stay here.

622
00:57:18.299 --> 00:57:19.843
I'll give you this place at a cheap price.

623
00:57:22.220 --> 00:57:23.930
Get him a first aid kit.

624
00:57:24.764 --> 00:57:26.891
and get some sleep. We'll leave after sundown.

625
00:57:46.620 --> 00:57:48.162
Why did you save me earlier?

626
00:57:49.498 --> 00:57:51.958
I was going to leave. but she wanted to save you.

627
00:57:52.959 --> 00:57:56.755
Dad told us we should help the weak
before he went to heaven.

628
00:57:57.922 --> 00:57:59.799
You looked weak.

629
00:58:02.051 --> 00:58:04.012
Stop yapping and go to bed.

630
00:58:04.095 --> 00:58:05.096
No!

631
00:58:05.179 --> 00:58:07.098
I'm going to bed soon too. so go to sleep!

632
00:58:07.181 --> 00:58:08.307
I don't want to!

633
00:58:08.725 --> 00:58:10.435
One! Two!

634
00:58:11.895 --> 00:58:13.021
She's always like that...

635
00:58:13.104 --> 00:58:14.648
She thinks she's so big now.

636
00:58:16.315 --> 00:58:17.901
Maybe we should've left you there.

637
00:58:18.527 --> 00:58:20.236
You're complaining when we saved you.

638
00:58:21.320 --> 00:58:22.781
You look like a zombie.

639
00:58:28.828 --> 00:58:31.164
Mm...

640
00:58:32.416 --> 00:58:34.501
How long does it take to get to Incheon Port?

641
00:58:34.584 --> 00:58:35.877
If we find an unobstructed route.

642
00:58:35.960 --> 00:58:37.336
it'll only take thirty minutes.

643
00:58:37.671 --> 00:58:39.631
Thirty minutes. thirty minutes. thirty minutes...

644
00:58:40.590 --> 00:58:42.133
What about zombies? Wouldn't it be dangerous?

645
00:58:42.216 --> 00:58:43.385
They bite and stuff.

646
00:58:43.468 --> 00:58:44.636
- Captain.
- Yes?

647
00:58:45.345 --> 00:58:47.138
We need to get out of here.

648
00:58:47.263 --> 00:58:49.140
Forget about the zombies!

649
00:58:50.058 --> 00:58:51.810
Should we bring Sergeant Hwang?

650
00:58:52.519 --> 00:58:55.063
He's more dangerous than the zombies.

651
00:58:55.146 --> 00:58:56.147
You're right.

652
00:58:56.230 --> 00:58:58.775
I can keep the gatekeepers off our backs.

653
00:58:59.359 --> 00:59:02.904
but sharp-witted Sergeant Hwang
might get suspicious.

654
00:59:04.823 --> 00:59:06.658
Yes. you're right.

655
00:59:07.701 --> 00:59:13.707
Then I just have to find a way
to distract him. right?

656
00:59:55.457 --> 00:59:57.000
Sir? Sir!

657
00:59:57.584 --> 00:59:59.919
Sir! Please!

658
01:00:00.462 --> 01:00:04.466
Sir! Please just take my girl!

659
01:00:07.969 --> 01:00:11.515
Jung-seok. why are you the only one alive?

660
01:00:45.882 --> 01:00:47.091
Put it down.

661
01:00:48.510 --> 01:00:49.761
You'll drain the batteries.

662
01:00:54.265 --> 01:00:57.101
Did Major Jane say she's coming to Incheon Port?

663
01:00:57.185 --> 01:00:58.269
Huh?

664
01:01:01.356 --> 01:01:04.317
She should. She has to.

665
01:01:06.653 --> 01:01:08.905
She better rescue my little darlings.

666
01:01:09.364 --> 01:01:10.824
My treasures.

667
01:01:11.991 --> 01:01:13.702
Yu-jin and Joon-i.

668
01:01:14.911 --> 01:01:17.664
they're the beacon of hope in this hell.

669
01:01:20.584 --> 01:01:25.755
I'll get them out of this hell no matter what.

670
01:01:28.925 --> 01:01:31.636
Major Jane is coming. right?

671
01:01:53.324 --> 01:01:54.368
Are you okay?

672
01:01:55.494 --> 01:01:59.163
We stole these when we fled. Take what you need.

673
01:02:02.501 --> 01:02:04.628
I actually saw you before.

674
01:02:05.420 --> 01:02:06.421
I...

675
01:02:07.005 --> 01:02:10.425
came across your family
when I was fleeing to board the ship.

676
01:02:12.135 --> 01:02:13.845
You begged me to take your girl.

677
01:02:18.642 --> 01:02:20.519
Why are you telling me that now?

678
01:02:21.936 --> 01:02:22.979
Because you feel guilty?

679
01:02:24.063 --> 01:02:25.273
There were 31 cars.

680
01:02:26.358 --> 01:02:28.234
There were 31 cars that drove past us.

681
01:02:29.444 --> 01:02:31.363
I thought the first car would stop to help us.

682
01:02:31.946 --> 01:02:33.322
Or maybe the next one...

683
01:02:37.619 --> 01:02:39.371
All 31 cars just drove by.

684
01:02:42.331 --> 01:02:44.042
You're indebted to my girls.

685
01:02:49.673 --> 01:02:52.008
Yu-jin. I'm buttoning you up.
Stand up straight!

686
01:02:53.134 --> 01:02:56.304
Are we going on a boat ride now?

687
01:02:56.388 --> 01:02:59.391
Yes. we just have to get something first.

688
01:03:03.102 --> 01:03:04.270
What about my cars?

689
01:03:04.604 --> 01:03:07.106
No way. we can't take them all.

690
01:03:10.527 --> 01:03:11.903
Then just this one!

691
01:03:12.236 --> 01:03:13.279
Put it down.

692
01:03:13.363 --> 01:03:15.031
Please. just one!

693
01:03:15.740 --> 01:03:17.367
Let me take one!

694
01:03:20.912 --> 01:03:21.955
Let's go.

695
01:04:12.547 --> 01:04:13.632
Joon-i.

696
01:04:14.383 --> 01:04:18.470
Stay here. If I'm not back by sunrise.
head back home.

697
01:04:19.095 --> 01:04:20.263
Just the three of us?

698
01:04:21.014 --> 01:04:22.223
What about you?

699
01:04:22.807 --> 01:04:24.100
How will you come home?

700
01:04:25.059 --> 01:04:26.936
I'll find my way somehow.

701
01:04:27.061 --> 01:04:28.813
so don't worry and head home.

702
01:04:30.732 --> 01:04:35.194
And don't ever leave the car. got it?

703
01:04:37.238 --> 01:04:38.239
Answer me.

704
01:04:40.409 --> 01:04:41.410
Okay.

705
01:04:43.412 --> 01:04:44.871
Yu-jin. come here.

706
01:04:48.750 --> 01:04:52.796
I'll be back soon. Listen to your sister. okay?

707
01:04:53.380 --> 01:04:55.339
You'll really be back soon. right?

708
01:04:55.632 --> 01:04:57.008
Of course. I'll be right back.

709
01:05:09.438 --> 01:05:12.566
Commander. take good care of my girls.

710
01:05:17.696 --> 01:05:18.738
Let's go.

711
01:06:20.592 --> 01:06:23.011
It's an emergency exit that we found
when we lived here.

712
01:06:58.755 --> 01:06:59.964
What the hell?

713
01:07:17.982 --> 01:07:19.067
Is that it?

714
01:07:22.571 --> 01:07:24.072
Yes. that's the one.

715
01:07:25.490 --> 01:07:26.658
Let's move quickly.

716
01:07:30.161 --> 01:07:31.996
Ah. ah. ah.

717
01:07:32.080 --> 01:07:34.749
I brought good news.

718
01:07:36.793 --> 01:07:42.924
Last night. the third platoon led by Sergeant Hwang

719
01:07:43.007 --> 01:07:44.468
brought home a truck.

720
01:07:45.093 --> 01:07:49.348
There was enough food for everyone to eat

721
01:07:49.431 --> 01:07:50.974
for an entire month.

722
01:07:55.979 --> 01:07:58.022
You've worked so hard. I know you did!

723
01:07:58.106 --> 01:08:03.151
So tonight... there'll be an unlimited game

724
01:08:03.236 --> 01:08:04.946
for 24 hours!

725
01:08:07.574 --> 01:08:09.951
And remember.

726
01:08:10.409 --> 01:08:12.579
Have fun like there's no tomorrow.

727
01:08:12.704 --> 01:08:13.872
Have a great time!

728
01:08:17.916 --> 01:08:21.044
There will be no tomorrow.

729
01:08:21.337 --> 01:08:25.091
Stop cheering. Doesn't he seem strange?

730
01:08:25.216 --> 01:08:26.342
I think he's high.

731
01:08:26.425 --> 01:08:28.887
I'm not sure. Let's enjoy this!

732
01:08:33.807 --> 01:08:36.353
Hey. look over there.

733
01:08:36.895 --> 01:08:38.021
Shouldn't we report that?

734
01:08:38.522 --> 01:08:41.525
There aren't that many. Why bother reporting?

735
01:08:42.359 --> 01:08:43.652
Forget it. don't mind them.

736
01:09:18.019 --> 01:09:19.145
Listen.

737
01:09:19.938 --> 01:09:21.690
Since you owe my girls.

738
01:09:23.149 --> 01:09:25.151
do me a favor later.

739
01:09:39.583 --> 01:09:43.336
Johnnie Walker Black Label!

740
01:09:46.673 --> 01:09:47.757
You're back.

741
01:09:49.175 --> 01:09:52.804
Are you supposed to have booze here?

742
01:09:52.887 --> 01:09:53.930
Well...

743
01:09:54.180 --> 01:09:57.559
The game is about to start. What brings you here?

744
01:09:57.642 --> 01:10:00.520
I haven't seen your face in ages.

745
01:10:01.396 --> 01:10:04.483
Could I have a sip?

746
01:10:04.566 --> 01:10:05.900
Sure. help yourself.

747
01:10:05.984 --> 01:10:07.151
- Really?
- Sure.

748
01:10:08.194 --> 01:10:10.447
So why are you here?

749
01:10:10.614 --> 01:10:12.907
Do you have something to report?

750
01:10:12.991 --> 01:10:17.412
No. I was just curious
what gets you up in the morning.

751
01:10:19.456 --> 01:10:20.832
Hm?

752
01:10:27.714 --> 01:10:28.757
It's good?

753
01:10:28.965 --> 01:10:30.216
So good!

754
01:10:32.093 --> 01:10:35.389
If you love it that much.
you can take the bottle.

755
01:10:35.972 --> 01:10:37.223
It's my gift to you.

756
01:10:39.017 --> 01:10:40.769
- What's with you?
- What?

757
01:10:41.853 --> 01:10:45.023
I begged for some snacks
for my boys to boost morale.

758
01:10:45.106 --> 01:10:46.858
but all we got were scraps.

759
01:10:47.859 --> 01:10:49.444
You were acting so cheap.

760
01:10:51.279 --> 01:10:52.989
So why the sudden generosity?

761
01:10:54.157 --> 01:10:56.701
I think I told everyone with my speech earlier.

762
01:10:57.619 --> 01:11:02.040
We owe so much to you and your men...

763
01:11:02.123 --> 01:11:03.166
Bullshit!

764
01:11:06.586 --> 01:11:09.798
I was just kidding.

765
01:11:11.007 --> 01:11:14.969
Captain Seo. are you hiding something from me?

766
01:11:16.971 --> 01:11:18.848
No. of course not.

767
01:11:22.101 --> 01:11:23.353
Captain Seo. I...

768
01:11:26.022 --> 01:11:27.106
Private Kim?

769
01:11:28.483 --> 01:11:31.152
Do you visit Captain Seo's quarters frequently?

770
01:11:32.904 --> 01:11:35.365
No... I do not.

771
01:11:59.764 --> 01:12:02.183
Ah.

772
01:12:03.935 --> 01:12:05.103
You two are a thing?

773
01:12:06.646 --> 01:12:08.314
- Yes.
- My apologies!

774
01:12:10.775 --> 01:12:13.277
I'm so clueless.

775
01:12:14.112 --> 01:12:15.238
I'll leave you two alone.

776
01:12:16.406 --> 01:12:17.532
Just the two of you...

777
01:12:17.616 --> 01:12:19.826
Hm?

778
01:12:20.619 --> 01:12:23.913
I'll tell the boys to avoid dropping in.

779
01:12:23.997 --> 01:12:25.164
so have a great time.

780
01:12:25.248 --> 01:12:28.752
Have a hot time. okay?

781
01:12:29.461 --> 01:12:30.504
All right.

782
01:12:31.295 --> 01:12:33.256
Love. love is...

783
01:12:35.174 --> 01:12:37.386
Sir. the preparation is done.
Shall we get to the truck?

784
01:12:37.469 --> 01:12:39.846
You go ahead. I have something to do first.

785
01:12:39.929 --> 01:12:40.930
Yes. sir.

786
01:12:43.141 --> 01:12:45.268
Does he have a death wish or what?

787
01:12:55.820 --> 01:12:59.366
Joon-i. look up ahead! Quickly!

788
01:13:09.333 --> 01:13:10.460
It's a march.

789
01:13:20.219 --> 01:13:22.556
That road is too close to Unit 631.

790
01:13:22.639 --> 01:13:24.349
Aren't we going to go greet Mom?

791
01:13:56.089 --> 01:13:57.298
The money is intact.

792
01:14:19.446 --> 01:14:22.449
Hey. can't you take me with you?

793
01:14:23.116 --> 01:14:24.576
I really want to get out of here.

794
01:14:25.827 --> 01:14:28.204
Go where? Who told you about that?

795
01:14:29.163 --> 01:14:32.125
I overheard Captain Seo talking
on the satellite phone.

796
01:14:32.876 --> 01:14:34.293
Please take me with you.

797
01:14:34.711 --> 01:14:36.045
Satellite phone?

798
01:14:36.671 --> 01:14:37.964
Where did you get it?

799
01:14:38.339 --> 01:14:40.759
The wild dog we found in the truck had it.

800
01:14:41.593 --> 01:14:42.761
Private Kim!

801
01:14:42.844 --> 01:14:44.346
Aren't you going to see the game?

802
01:14:45.722 --> 01:14:47.140
Answer naturally.

803
01:14:50.268 --> 01:14:51.436
I'm all right.

804
01:14:51.936 --> 01:14:53.605
You always say that. Oh. right.

805
01:14:54.022 --> 01:14:56.608
That wild dog who came with the truck.

806
01:14:56.691 --> 01:14:58.317
that guy was no joke.

807
01:14:58.693 --> 01:15:01.946
He was struggling so much to survive.

808
01:15:03.114 --> 01:15:05.033
I bet all my canned goods on him!

809
01:15:05.909 --> 01:15:06.993
I'll see you later.

810
01:15:08.745 --> 01:15:10.329
Where is the phone now?

811
01:15:10.789 --> 01:15:12.290
It's not with me.

812
01:15:12.374 --> 01:15:13.958
Captain Seo has it. He'll be here soon.

813
01:15:18.087 --> 01:15:19.297
Get going.

814
01:15:20.339 --> 01:15:21.633
I can't wait long.

815
01:15:28.014 --> 01:15:31.059
Act naturally when that bastard comes. got it?

816
01:15:32.686 --> 01:15:33.770
Okay...

817
01:15:35.271 --> 01:15:37.732
Number 61!

818
01:16:00.380 --> 01:16:01.756
What are you doing? Let's move!

819
01:16:03.717 --> 01:16:05.009
Captain...

820
01:16:06.470 --> 01:16:08.012
Long time no see. Captain Seo.

821
01:16:09.723 --> 01:16:11.891
Min-jung. you were alive. Gosh.

822
01:16:12.934 --> 01:16:14.728
You have the satellite phone. right?

823
01:16:14.811 --> 01:16:15.937
Hand it over.

824
01:16:17.897 --> 01:16:19.148
The satellite phone...

825
01:16:19.816 --> 01:16:20.942
Give me a second.

826
01:16:21.776 --> 01:16:23.362
Mm. Oh.

827
01:16:37.125 --> 01:16:38.167
Wasn't that a gunshot?

828
01:16:38.251 --> 01:16:40.003
Like hell it was. Just shut up and eat this tuna.

829
01:16:40.086 --> 01:16:41.129
Hey!

830
01:16:46.134 --> 01:16:47.176
Oh.

831
01:16:49.554 --> 01:16:50.639
Let's go get Mom.

832
01:17:07.614 --> 01:17:09.408
Look! That bastard!

833
01:17:14.287 --> 01:17:15.747
Gun! Get the guns!

834
01:17:19.333 --> 01:17:21.044
- Are you okay?
- Yes...

835
01:17:21.711 --> 01:17:22.712
Can you get up?

836
01:17:23.171 --> 01:17:25.089
Yes. I can get up. I can get up.

837
01:17:32.431 --> 01:17:33.682
Stay behind me.

838
01:17:36.309 --> 01:17:38.687
Hey. where did he go?

839
01:17:39.020 --> 01:17:40.021
Jesus Christ...

840
01:17:42.273 --> 01:17:45.485
Min-jung. I was so worried...

841
01:17:47.571 --> 01:17:49.489
That's mine. give it back...

842
01:17:53.368 --> 01:17:54.411
Sergeant!

843
01:17:56.455 --> 01:17:58.122
Where did that bastard go?

844
01:18:02.419 --> 01:18:03.628
Go look for him.

845
01:18:11.094 --> 01:18:12.261
Block the entrance!

846
01:18:16.433 --> 01:18:17.476
Move!

847
01:19:07.442 --> 01:19:08.652
Fire! Fire!

848
01:19:35.762 --> 01:19:37.138
Hey. Go forward.

849
01:20:06.292 --> 01:20:07.293
Damn it!

850
01:20:07.461 --> 01:20:08.462
Jung-seok!

851
01:20:24.310 --> 01:20:25.395
Sergeant!

852
01:21:09.439 --> 01:21:10.649
Come on!

853
01:21:54.818 --> 01:21:57.404
Hurry! Get in!

854
01:22:02.033 --> 01:22:03.910
Get in! Come on!

855
01:22:08.122 --> 01:22:09.499
Snap out of it!

856
01:22:10.208 --> 01:22:11.460
Come on!

857
01:22:12.877 --> 01:22:13.962
Hurry!

858
01:22:34.358 --> 01:22:37.361
Go after them!

859
01:22:52.125 --> 01:22:53.918
Captain. are you okay?

860
01:22:57.046 --> 01:22:58.214
What do we do now. sir?

861
01:23:01.510 --> 01:23:02.594
Captain!

862
01:23:10.852 --> 01:23:12.521
You did all you can.

863
01:23:13.021 --> 01:23:14.313
That's what matters.

864
01:23:14.648 --> 01:23:15.774
Get it together.

865
01:23:40.715 --> 01:23:41.800
Sergeant Hwang!

866
01:23:43.802 --> 01:23:44.886
Step on it!

867
01:23:48.222 --> 01:23:52.060
It's time for us. To say goodbye

868
01:23:52.686 --> 01:23:54.729
Let's meet again soon

869
01:25:08.720 --> 01:25:09.804
Grandpa. hurry!

870
01:25:10.179 --> 01:25:11.556
Okay!

871
01:25:14.976 --> 01:25:16.227
Open the window.

872
01:25:39.501 --> 01:25:40.877
Mom!

873
01:25:41.378 --> 01:25:44.005
We came to greet you!

874
01:25:44.088 --> 01:25:46.340
Why don't you ever listen to me?

875
01:25:47.592 --> 01:25:48.718
Come on!

876
01:26:02.732 --> 01:26:03.942
Yee-haw!

877
01:26:29.217 --> 01:26:31.345
- Hold on.
- Okay!

878
01:27:00.289 --> 01:27:05.379
Hey! Stop with the damn flares!
Just kill them all!

879
01:27:25.314 --> 01:27:26.441
They're behind us!

880
01:27:32.822 --> 01:27:33.990
Hold on tight!

881
01:27:47.504 --> 01:27:48.713
Come on!

882
01:27:58.765 --> 01:28:00.684
You asshole!

883
01:28:08.983 --> 01:28:10.193
He's not bad.

884
01:28:56.656 --> 01:28:58.617
Pull up closer. asshole!

885
01:28:58.700 --> 01:29:00.118
This way. move up!

886
01:29:01.285 --> 01:29:02.286
Kill him!

887
01:29:17.802 --> 01:29:19.262
Watch the front. asshole!

888
01:29:19.638 --> 01:29:20.722
Hold the wheel!

889
01:29:22.724 --> 01:29:23.725
Hey!

890
01:29:33.943 --> 01:29:35.028
Turn on the lights.

891
01:30:00.720 --> 01:30:01.971
To our right!

892
01:30:18.780 --> 01:30:19.823
Beside you!

893
01:30:44.013 --> 01:30:45.014
Watch out!

894
01:31:30.477 --> 01:31:31.603
Hold on tight!

895
01:32:45.385 --> 01:32:46.720
Go over to the right!

896
01:33:17.959 --> 01:33:20.253
Hey! Back up. back up. back up!

897
01:33:26.009 --> 01:33:28.219
Back it up!

898
01:33:29.679 --> 01:33:32.599
I said back it up. asshole!

899
01:33:36.310 --> 01:33:38.104
Just step on it!

900
01:33:39.188 --> 01:33:41.525
Back the shit up!

901
01:33:42.316 --> 01:33:44.193
What the hell are you doing? Back it up!

902
01:33:48.281 --> 01:33:49.366
You bastard!

903
01:34:15.475 --> 01:34:16.768
We're almost there.

904
01:34:26.945 --> 01:34:29.614
We arrive at Incheon Port in 15 minutes.

905
01:35:04.816 --> 01:35:05.817
Joon-i.

906
01:35:06.443 --> 01:35:09.237
Is that the boat? Oh. yes!

907
01:35:20.415 --> 01:35:21.458
Yu-jin...

908
01:35:22.250 --> 01:35:23.377
Yu-jin. are you okay?

909
01:35:24.669 --> 01:35:25.712
Hi.

910
01:35:29.090 --> 01:35:30.091
Joon-i!

911
01:35:32.886 --> 01:35:35.304
Put down your gun! Come on!

912
01:35:37.306 --> 01:35:38.392
Drop it!

913
01:35:38.933 --> 01:35:40.935
Do you want to see her head blown up?

914
01:35:41.019 --> 01:35:42.103
Put it down!

915
01:35:47.150 --> 01:35:49.569
Kick it! Kick it away!

916
01:35:50.487 --> 01:35:51.905
Yes. that's it.

917
01:35:55.909 --> 01:35:57.994
I can finally get off this peninsula...

918
01:35:58.703 --> 01:36:03.750
When I leave. I'm going to live
to the fullest in Hong Kong.

919
01:36:06.127 --> 01:36:09.130
They won't know what I did here.

920
01:36:09.506 --> 01:36:11.466
I'm going to be a good man.

921
01:36:12.216 --> 01:36:15.637
Thank you. Thank you so much.

922
01:36:15.720 --> 01:36:17.305
I'll thank you every night.

923
01:36:17.764 --> 01:36:19.933
I really mean it. Thank you so much.

924
01:36:20.016 --> 01:36:22.436
I love you all!

925
01:36:22.519 --> 01:36:23.520
Now!

926
01:36:26.523 --> 01:36:27.524
Okay...

927
01:36:33.613 --> 01:36:34.614
No!

928
01:37:05.979 --> 01:37:07.439
Grandpa...

929
01:37:08.398 --> 01:37:11.150
Grandpa. are you okay?

930
01:37:11.526 --> 01:37:12.777
Grandpa...

931
01:37:12.986 --> 01:37:14.571
Mom! Mom...

932
01:37:48.187 --> 01:37:49.272
The sun is rising.

933
01:37:49.356 --> 01:37:50.357
A horde's coming.

934
01:37:50.940 --> 01:37:52.108
We have to depart!

935
01:38:04.037 --> 01:38:05.121
The money's here.

936
01:38:08.417 --> 01:38:09.418
Huh?

937
01:38:10.502 --> 01:38:12.045
It's not him.

938
01:38:13.505 --> 01:38:15.214
How many times did they switch?

939
01:38:18.134 --> 01:38:19.344
Nice to meet you...

940
01:38:19.969 --> 01:38:22.180
- Nice to meet you too.
- Thank you.

941
01:38:29.729 --> 01:38:32.774
Get rid of the body!

942
01:38:46.996 --> 01:38:50.459
Hey. stop!

943
01:39:00.469 --> 01:39:03.388
Get the money!

944
01:39:03.472 --> 01:39:06.391
Shut the back hatch! Zombies are coming!

945
01:39:39.048 --> 01:39:41.760
Grandpa...

946
01:39:44.471 --> 01:39:47.349
Okay. I'm okay...

947
01:39:47.849 --> 01:39:50.101
Grandpa...

948
01:39:53.938 --> 01:39:56.941
I wanted to pull you out of this hell...

949
01:40:00.194 --> 01:40:01.363
No...

950
01:40:02.822 --> 01:40:05.534
We were together all along.

951
01:40:06.993 --> 01:40:08.995
Why would this be hell?

952
01:40:11.039 --> 01:40:12.081
Thank you...

953
01:40:12.999 --> 01:40:14.918
Grandpa...

954
01:40:18.963 --> 01:40:20.590
Grandpa!

955
01:40:22.175 --> 01:40:23.635
I'm sorry...

956
01:40:25.136 --> 01:40:27.431
for making you live in this world...

957
01:40:27.806 --> 01:40:29.933
Grandpa...

958
01:40:31.560 --> 01:40:35.397
- Grandpa...
- I'm sorry...

959
01:40:35.647 --> 01:40:37.065
Grandpa.

960
01:40:42.654 --> 01:40:44.113
Grandpa!

961
01:40:49.243 --> 01:40:50.995
Don't die...

962
01:40:56.084 --> 01:40:58.795
Grandpa! No!

963
01:41:01.214 --> 01:41:02.757
Grandpa...

964
01:41:43.339 --> 01:41:45.049
Girls! The fireworks!

965
01:41:45.133 --> 01:41:46.175
Hurry!

966
01:41:47.636 --> 01:41:48.637
Joon-i!

967
01:41:55.226 --> 01:41:58.647
You promised to do a favor for me.

968
01:41:59.981 --> 01:42:02.942
Take the girls with you no matter what.

969
01:42:03.777 --> 01:42:04.819
Got it?

970
01:42:05.153 --> 01:42:06.154
Promise me. okay?

971
01:42:06.905 --> 01:42:07.947
Get going!

972
01:42:08.740 --> 01:42:09.741
Now!

973
01:42:24.172 --> 01:42:27.300
Commander. thank you.

974
01:43:14.639 --> 01:43:16.891
Mom's falling behind!

975
01:44:19.037 --> 01:44:20.204
Are you all right?

976
01:44:20.414 --> 01:44:21.581
You're safe now!

977
01:44:25.334 --> 01:44:26.335
Jane...

978
01:44:26.420 --> 01:44:27.421
Jane!

979
01:44:27.504 --> 01:44:30.465
Jane! We have to save my mom!

980
01:44:30.549 --> 01:44:31.883
I'm sorry. It's too late!

981
01:44:31.966 --> 01:44:33.176
We can't put you in danger.

982
01:44:33.259 --> 01:44:34.344
We must leave now!

983
01:44:34.428 --> 01:44:37.180
Please. help my mom!

984
01:44:37.889 --> 01:44:39.391
Please! Just this once!

985
01:44:39.558 --> 01:44:40.559
Go! Let's go!

986
01:44:40.850 --> 01:44:41.851
Let's go!

987
01:44:41.935 --> 01:44:43.102
You must wait!

988
01:44:45.814 --> 01:44:46.856
Please...

989
01:44:48.442 --> 01:44:50.402
Remain calm...

990
01:45:00.787 --> 01:45:02.163
Don't wait for me...

991
01:45:26.480 --> 01:45:27.481
No...

992
01:45:28.898 --> 01:45:29.899
Mom!

993
01:45:29.983 --> 01:45:32.777
Don't do it. Mom!

994
01:45:42.203 --> 01:45:43.246
Let go of me!

995
01:45:46.875 --> 01:45:47.876
Mom!

996
01:45:57.010 --> 01:45:58.637
Mom. please!

997
01:46:06.728 --> 01:46:09.523
She made a very sensible decision.

998
01:46:10.189 --> 01:46:14.068
It was for the best! For everyone...

999
01:46:15.194 --> 01:46:16.863
Sensible decision. my ass.

1000
01:46:18.907 --> 01:46:20.074
Did you even try?

1001
01:46:22.869 --> 01:46:23.870
Jung-seok...

1002
01:46:25.246 --> 01:46:26.748
You're tormented too!

1003
01:46:28.458 --> 01:46:29.793
You just gave up!

1004
01:46:29.876 --> 01:46:32.504
We have to save Mom!

1005
01:46:39.469 --> 01:46:41.054
I'll bring back your mom.

1006
01:46:42.263 --> 01:46:43.473
Wait right here.

1007
01:46:55.485 --> 01:46:57.696
Mom! Run!

1008
01:48:28.828 --> 01:48:31.205
- Mom!
- Mom!

1009
01:48:38.797 --> 01:48:39.798
Mom!

1010
01:49:56.791 --> 01:49:59.628
Don't worry. She'll be okay.

1011
01:50:04.383 --> 01:50:05.675
She'll be fine.

1012
01:50:19.523 --> 01:50:22.233
In a few hours. a new world will be waiting.

1013
01:50:24.027 --> 01:50:27.781
The world I knew wasn't bad either.
